Ad Text:
The Opportunity

A leading financial services organisation is seeking a Senior Manager, Project Finance to join a central finance function responsible for groupwide investment and expense financial management.

This is a senior leadership role with accountability for delivering high-quality financial services across investment portfolios, including reporting, forecasting, analytics, cost control, and governance. You will partner closely with Finance leadership and senior business stakeholders to deliver forward-looking commercial insights, strengthen financial controls, and uplift enterprise-wide capability.

Key Responsibilities
Lead groupwide investment financial servicing, including month-end close, forecasting, reporting, and analytics
Drive robust expense management, financial control, and governance frameworks
Deliver insights on investment cost drivers, risks, opportunities, and benchmarking
Establish and optimise standardised investment finance services, processes, and service levels
Lead and develop a high-performing team, including offshore resources
Partner with senior Finance and business leaders on strategically important initiatives
Support transformation, continuous improvement, and capability uplift across investment finance
About You
CA/CPA qualified (or equivalent)
Strong background in investment finance, expense management, or portfolio financial management
Experience operating in large, complex, matrixed organisations (banking or financial services preferred)
Proven people leader with experience managing large and/or offshore teams
Strong commercial mindset with advanced analytical and problem-solving skills
Solid understanding of financial control frameworks, SOX, and risk management
Experience with finance systems and tools such as GL, TM1, Power BI, Excel, and portfolio tools highly regarded
Exposure to Lean, Six Sigma, or transformation environments is advantageous
Why Apply?
Senior, high-impact role with enterprise-wide visibility
Hybrid working model based in Sydney CBD
Opportunity to shape investment finance services at scale
Strong leadership, transformation, and career development exposure

Ad Text:
Employment Type: Full-Time (35 hours p/week)
Duration: 12 Month Fixed-Term Contract
Remuneration: Salary determined after interview, commensurate with skills & experience
Location: UNSW Kensington Campus

About UNSW:
UNSW isn’t like other places you’ve worked. Yes, we’re a large organisation with a diverse and talented community, a community doing extraordinary things. Together, we are driven to be thoughtful, practical, and purposeful in all we do. Taking this combined approach is what makes our work matter. If you want a career where you can thrive, be challenged and do meaningful work, you’re in the right place.

Why Your Role Matters:
This is an exciting opportunity for an experienced Program Manager with strong Business Analyst capability to lead the planning, development and delivery of major improvement initiatives at UNSW. Reporting to the Enterprise Portfolio Management Office (EPMO), you will be deployed to a major transformation program.

In this role, you will shape and deliver a complex program of work, overseeing planning and execution across each phase of delivery. You will apply a strong analytical and problem-solving approach to support requirements definition, process analysis and informed decision making. Working closely with senior leaders and stakeholders across faculties and divisions, you will ensure alignment, collaboration and effective delivery across multiple interdependent workstreams.

You will bring proven experience in large scale program delivery, strong Business Analyst expertise, and well developed leadership and stakeholder management skills to drive outcomes that enhance UNSW’s operations and community impact.

The role reports to the Program Director.

Responsibilities Include:

Lead and advise on program delivery to achieve strategic objectives, benefits, and value.
Develop and manage the program master plan, covering schedules, milestones, budgets, risks, and dependencies.
Support project owners in securing and managing funding through business cases, stage gates, and post-investment reviews.
Provide insights on market trends and business strategies to guide prioritisation and maximise benefits.
Ensure alignment with University governance and EPMO project management frameworks.
Build and manage strong relationships with senior stakeholders across academic and professional portfolios.
Foster a customer-centric culture and deliver clear, effective program communications.
Oversee reporting on program scope, schedule, resources, finances, risks, and benefits.
Anticipate, escalate, and mitigate risks to maintain program performance.
Lead and develop a team of Project Managers and Officers, ensuring consistent delivery across all projects.

For more information regarding the responsibilities for this role, please refer to the Position Description at JOBS@UNSW.

Skills and Experience Summary:

Relevant tertiary qualifications or equivalent professional experience.
Significant hands-on experience working in a dedicated Business Analyst role, including requirements elicitation, process mapping and documentation.
Proven experience in workload planning and resource management across diverse teams.
Extensive background as a program director leading complex, high-impact programs in dynamic environments.
Strong expertise in program governance and delivery using a range of project management methodologies.
Exceptional written communication skills, with the ability to produce clear, persuasive reports, proposals, and executive papers.
Demonstrated leadership and team management skills, fostering collaboration and professional credibility across stakeholders.
High-level problem-solving, continuous improvement, and risk management capabilities, with adaptability to change.
Sound financial literacy, with experience managing budgets and controlling expenditure.
Comprehensive understanding of core project management competencies including scope, time, cost, quality, risk, and stakeholder engagement.

Benefits and Culture: People are at the core of everything we do. We recognise it is the contributions of our staff who make UNSW one of the best universities in Australia and the world.  Our benefits include: 

Career development opportunities 
17% Superannuation contributions
Additional 3 days of leave over Christmas period 
Discounts and entitlements (retail, education, fitness)

Job details




The Business Analyst - Enterprise Analytics & Integration ("Analytics BA") will work within the Enterprise Analytics & Integration team to deliver high‑quality data and analytics solutions. The role combines traditional business analysis capability with strong data literacy, enabling the translation of business needs into actionable and technically feasible analytics outcomes.

The position requires strong skills in eliciting and documenting requirements, user story creation, process analysis, and functional specifications, paired with applied experience in data storytelling, dashboard design, wireframing, and close collaboration with BI developers, and subject matter experts.

The role focuses on supporting enterprise analytics delivery using primary analytics platforms, particularly SAP BW and SAP Analytics Cloud (SAC).




Key duties and responsibilities



Engage stakeholders, SMEs and data custodians to elicit and analyse analytics and reporting requirements.
Translate requirements into clear User Stories, acceptance criteria, process maps and functional specifications.
Design and iterate dashboard wireframes and conceptual data models with stakeholders.
Apply data storytelling practices to guide design, highlight insights, and improve adoption.
Work with BI developers to ensure feasibility and alignment with enterprise data models, SAP BW/4HANA structures, and SAC capabilities.
Support end‑to‑end analytics delivery including design, development support, UAT coordination, documentation and handover.
Promote best‑practice reporting, data governance, and enterprise analytics standards.
Contribute to EAI's analytics roadmap and deliver enterprise analytics products within an agile delivery environment.

Summary

As a Senior Finance Analyst, you’ll be at the heart of one of Australia’s most significant aviation programs – OneSKY. This is your chance to influence strategic decisions, drive financial excellence, and embed commercial discipline across a portfolio that’s transforming how Australia flies.

The Organisation

Airservices Australia is a government-owned organisation responsible for the safe and efficient management of 11% of the world’s airspace and provision of aviation rescue fire fighting services at Australia’s busiest airports.

Our people are our greatest asset with a dynamic and diverse team operating from locations across the country - from bustling cities to regional and remote locations, including an island. This team are helping to secure the future of Australia’s skies and keep it amongst the safest in the world.

We connect people with their world safely – linking family and friends, generating economic activity, creating jobs, and facilitating trade and tourism.

Airservices is committed to fostering a culture that is diverse, inclusive, and respectful.  We encourage motivated individuals who love what they do, value a service first mindset and embrace a challenge to explore a career with Airservices. In return you will be a valued team member, be offered flexibility and experience a meaningful career in an exciting, ever-evolving aviation industry.

The Role & The Team

We are seeking a Senior Portfolio Finance Analyst to join our OneSKY Program. This pivotal role provides strategic financial and commercial support to the OneSKY Portfolio, ensuring robust financial frameworks, governance, and transparency across all investment spend. You will work closely with the Portfolio Head and Finance Director to deliver insights that drive value and uplift commercial acumen across the organisation.

Key Responsibilities

Deliver insightful portfolio investment reporting and analysis to support decision-making.
Lead the implementation and continuous improvement of financial control and reporting frameworks.
Manage portfolio financial planning, including annual OPEX/CAPEX budgets and 5-year investment plans.
Oversee month-end finance activities, reconciliations, forecasts, and variance analysis.
Support business case development, benefit realisation models, and investment submissions.
Provide financial assessment of tenders and manage asset accounting processes.
Coach and develop team members to enhance financial and commercial capability.

Please see the link below to view the full Position Description:

 PD - OneSKY Snr Finance Analyst.pdf

The Person

You are a commercially astute finance professional with:

10+ years’ experience in financial or commercial management roles.
Strong understanding of asset accounting principles and lifecycle management.
Proven ability to deliver financial insights and make sound decisions in complex environments.
Experience with ERP systems (e.g., SAP) and reporting tools.
Excellent stakeholder engagement, communication, and influencing skills.
A tertiary qualification in Accounting/Finance or related field; CPA/CA membership highly desirable.

 

At Airservices Australia, we embrace and thrive on diversity of thought, perspectives, and capabilities because we know the benefits of having a workforce that is representative of the community that we serve. We appreciate everyone is unique, and acknowledge diversity in thought leads to greater transparency and improved consideration in our decision making.

We believe a diverse workforce supported by an inclusive culture is central to our success. We actively encourage and welcome candidates from all cultural backgrounds, gender identities, people living with disability and Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples to apply.

The Senior Solutions Consultant is a pivotal pre-sales role within IBM, responsible for driving complex solution pursuits, shaping strategic opportunities and influencing high-value customer engagements across the public sector and the broader opportunity landscape. We are seeking a dynamic, highly technical and commercially astute professional who brings strong client-facing capability, deep solution design expertise, and the ability to communicate value effectively to both technical and senior executive stakeholders.
This role requires the ability to craft competitive, differentiated, and deliverable solutions that solve client challenges in a disruptive, forward-thinking, and strategically bold manner— ultimately positioning IBM as the partner of choice in mission-critical, large-scale pursuits.

The position reports directly to the Head of Solutions for ANZ, working closely with Sector leaders, sales teams, client partners and technical SMEs to steer opportunity strategy and strengthen IBM’s presence across key industries.

Your Roles and Responsibilities*

Primary focal point for all public sector opportunities as the Lead Solutions Consultant.
Shape pursuit strategy with sales, legal, delivery, and industry teams to build competitive and compliant solution offerings.
Perform competitive analysis of public sector providers and articulate IBM’s strengths in capability, compliance, security, and delivery scale.
Manage end-to-end government tender processes (RFT, RFQ, EOI), including response strategy and compliance with the sales team.
Produce high-quality and fully compliant tender submissions aligned to mandatory criteria, weightings, and evaluation frameworks.
Structure and Develop solutions (using SFIA-based roles, rate cards, or outcome-based approaches), ensuring alignment to public sector expectations and competitive benchmarks.
Develop solution artefacts including delivery models, governance structures, commercial constructs, cost models, pricing scenarios, Project Schedule and content for the responses.
Craft clear, differentiated value propositions addressing risk, cost transparency, sovereign requirements, compliance expectations and long-term capability uplift.
Prepare, Develop and Lead orals presentations, confidently defend the solution and articulating key value drivers during client evaluations.
Ensure proposed solutions are feasible, compliant, deliverable, and aligned with IBM standards and government procurement constraints.

Required Professional and Technical Expertise:

- Public Sector Experience: Proven track record in federal and state government deals, including navigating tender processes (RFT, RFQ, EOI) and understanding procurement policies and evaluation frameworks.
- Pre-Sales & Solutioning: Strong background in pre-sales, consulting, developing services-led solutions, and leading complex, multi-stakeholder pursuits.
- Client-Facing Skills: Ability to engage with senior stakeholders, influence decision-making and communicate value propositions clearly and persuasively.
- Strategic Thinking: Ability to shape pursuit strategy, position IBM competitively, and anticipate client needs in complex, regulated environments.
- Commercial Acumen: Understanding of pricing models, cost structures, rate cards (including SFIA-based), and contract/commercial considerations in public sector deals
- Collaboration & Leadership: Partner effectively across sales, delivery, legal, and industry teams to build aligned, compliant, and competitive solutions.
- A Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Information Systems, Engineering or a related discipline (or equivalent experience).
- Strong understanding of one key technical domain such as Hybrid cloud, integration, security standards, enterprise architecture concepts and modern delivery models.
- Ability to translate technical requirements into deliverable solution constructs and articulate technical outcomes in non-technical language.
- Familiarity with government security classifications, IRAP, ASD Essential Eight, and sovereign hosting considerations (desirable).
- Additional training or credentials in solution architecture, commercial management, or public sector procurement are advantageous.
- Proficiency in Microsoft PowerPoint for developing polished orals presentations, solution narratives, and executive-ready decks. Strong oral and written communication skills
- Advanced Microsoft Excel skills for cost modelling, pricing analysis, scenario modelling and interpreting complex datasets to meaningful solution approaches
- Strong capability in evaluation and assessment techniques for analysing RFI/RFP responses, selection criteria, scoring frameworks and weightings.

FOREVER US

Step into the world of Forever New, where fashion meets innovation and every experience is designed to make it her moment. From our Melbourne beginnings over 20 years ago to more than 450 stores globally, Forever New continues to evolve - blending beautiful fashion with smart, scalable technology that supports our teams and delights our customers.

As we continue to grow and transform our retail and digital landscape, we’re looking for a Senior Business Analyst to play a critical role in shaping the systems and processes that power our stores, supply chain, and digital channels.

THE PERKS WE OFFER YOU

As part of the Forever New family, you’ll enjoy benefits designed to support your success and wellbeing:

Generous 40% staff discount, plus family and friends’ discounts
Subsidised daily coffee and lunch at our on-site cafe
Subsidised parking at our vibrant Richmond Head Office
Loyalty and birthday leave to celebrate life’s milestones
Referral incentives for introducing great talent to our team
Access to wellbeing and sustainability initiatives
Continuous learning and development opportunities
Recognition through reward and service awards programs
Exposure to a global retail and technology environment

 

YOUR DREAM OPPORTUNITY

As the Senior Business Analyst, you’ll be responsible for ensuring our retail systems and processes effectively support business operations and customer outcomes. Reporting to the Digital Solutions Manager, you’ll work closely with stakeholders across stores, supply chain, head office, and technology teams to translate business needs into clear, practical, and high-quality technology solutions.

This is a hands-on, end-to-end role where you’ll influence how our POS, WMS, ERP, and merchandising platforms evolve - driving efficiency, data accuracy, and continuous improvement across the business.

GET EXCITED TO:

Lead end-to-end business analysis activities across retail, store operations, supply chain, and digital channels
Gather, analyse, and document business requirements for core retail systems including POS, WMS, ERP, and planning platforms
Facilitate workshops, interviews, and process-mapping sessions with stakeholders across stores, head office, and distribution centres
Translate business needs into clear user stories, functional and non-functional requirements, and acceptance criteria
Map current-state and future-state processes to identify gaps, inefficiencies, and improvement opportunities
Partner with technical teams to support solution design and ensure alignment with business and operational realities
Support system implementations, upgrades, and integrations across retail technology platforms
Develop and execute test plans, coordinate UAT, and validate solutions prior to deployment
Collaborate with vendors and third-party partners to clarify requirements, review deliverables, and ensure solution quality
Support change management activities including training materials, communications, and post-go-live support
Contribute to project planning, risk assessment, and prioritisation discussions
Maintain accurate documentation, process flows, and knowledge repositories
Drive continuous improvement by identifying and addressing technical debt

THE SKILLS & EXPERIENCE YOU OFFER US

Minimum 7 years of experience in IT, including proven success as a Business Analyst for at least 3+ years within mid-sized retail organizations.
Demonstrated expertise in leading business analysis for the implementation or replacement of core retail systems, including WMS, ERP platforms, POS, and Merchandising/Planning solutions. Omnichannel projects are desirable.
In-depth understanding of retail operations, store processes, and POS environments, with a focus on improving efficiency and customer experience.
Track record of delivering IT projects in fast-paced, dynamic environments with cross-functional teams.
Advanced analytical and problem-solving skills, with strong attention to detail and a commitment to quality documentation.
Proficient in business process mapping and modelling using tools such as Microsoft Visio and Lucidchart.
Skilled in Agile delivery frameworks and MoSCoW prioritization techniques, and collaboration tools including Jira and Confluence.
Exceptional communication and stakeholder engagement abilities, with the capacity to influence and align diverse teams.
Experience leading end-to-end business analysis across multiple projects while supporting BAU.
Adept at facilitating workshops, conducting stakeholder interviews, and defining future-state solutions through process mapping and requirements gathering.
Capable of producing comprehensive documentation including user stories, functional and non-functional specifications, business rules, schema mappings, and process flows.
Contributed to small-scale project delivery with opportunities to assume project management responsibilities.
Provide mentorship and oversight to peers, promoting consistency and adherence to best-practice standards.
Developed and executed test strategies, coordinated user acceptance testing (UAT), and ensured solutions met defined acceptance criteria.
Supported change management efforts including training development, communication planning, and post-implementation support.
Actively participated in project planning, risk assessment, and solution design to ensure alignment with business goals.

 

BEHAVIOURS & ATTRIBUTES

Strong analytical and problem-solving capability
Collaborative and relationship-focused, with excellent stakeholder engagement skills
Results-driven, with the ability to prioritise and deliver to deadlines
Calm, adaptable, and resilient under pressure
Clear and confident communicator, both written and verbal
Proactive mindset with a passion for continuous improvement

 

OUR VALUES

Everything we do at Forever New is guided by our values:
Think Customer
Respect for All
Keep it Simple
Take Responsibility
Act with Pace

Join Forever New and play a key role in shaping the technology and processes that support our people, our customers, and our continued global growth

Ad Text:
The Company

This organisation is a well-established, mid–large enterprise with a strong reputation for quality, governance and professionalism. The finance function is highly regarded internally and is led by an experienced, supportive leadership team that values collaboration, continuous improvement and high performance.

The culture is collegiate, delivery-focused and inclusive, with senior finance leaders who genuinely invest in process excellence and developing best practice across reporting and controls.

Offices are based in Melbourne's south east so ideal for anyone living locally who is comfortable working on site Monay - Friday.

The Position

This is a 9-month fixed-term contract commencing late January or early February, based 5 days on site in Melbourne’s south eastern suburbs.

Reporting to the Head of Finance, the Financial Reporting Manager will act as a senior technical lead responsible for the integrity of the general ledger and all local and parent company reporting. The role plays a critical part in month-end, quarter-end and year-end close and provides senior-level backup and overflow support during peak periods.

Key duties will involve:

Completion of accurate and timely financial reporting and optimisation of reporting and financial processes to increase accuracy, minimise internal control gaps and manage risk
Ensuring that daily accounting functions are performed accurately by local teams and that parent company reporting is completed within timeframe
Documentation of financial policies and procedures in line with internal audit requirements
Remediation of audit items within agreed timeframe
Responding to and resolve complex financial queries from internal finance team or various department leaders

In addition to core reporting responsibilities, this role offers genuine scope to:

Improve, streamline and automate reporting processes
Reduce manual intervention and control risk using Power Query / BI solutions
Contribute to ad hoc, project-based work across finance and the wider business
The environment is fast paced and will suit someone comfortable operating with autonomy, minimal hand-holding and competing deadlines.

Why Apply?
Immediate impact role with visibility at senior finance leadership level
Highly collaborative team with strong leadership and clear direction
Opportunity to drive process improvement and automation, not just “keep the lights on”
Exposure to complex reporting and governance requirements within a mature organisation
Well-structured finance function with strong controls and audit discipline
Ideal location for anyone seeking an opportunity in the south east
Chance to start quickly and secure a great role lasting for the bulk of 2026
The Successful Candidate Profile

You will be a senior accounting professional who thrives in hands-on, delivery-focused environments and is comfortable stepping into a leadership-capacity role from day one.

Key requirements include:

CA or CPA qualification with 10+ years’ experience in mid to large organisations
Strong management reporting experience
Demonstrated ability to lead through influence, provide senior-level backup and manage complex ad hoc requests
Proven process improvement mindset with a track record of automating or optimising reporting
Advanced experience with Power Query, Power BI or similar automated BI tools
Strong understanding of financial controls, audit requirements and risk management
Ability to operate at pace, prioritise effectively and meet tight deadlines
This role will suit someone who enjoys being “in the detail” while also thinking strategically about how finance can operate better, faster and with lower risk.

Bring a human‑centred lens to AI adoption and help shape how customers and employees experience emerging technology, while building your career in a growing innovation function.

About the Role

As an AI Adoption Specialist, you will support the successful adoption of AI by designing and validating customer and employee experiences across claims and customer service initiatives. Strong planning, analytical and business acumen are essential, along with a proactive, solutions‑focused approach to meeting deadlines, targets and reporting requirements with minimal supervision.

 

Key Responsibilities include

Developing and managing enterprise‑wide analytics and reporting frameworks to deliver timely, accurate and actionable insights.
Providing operational, financial and performance analysis to support data‑driven decision‑making across the business.
Ensuring data integrity, reliability and compliance within agreed governance and portfolio tolerances.
Supporting resource, cost, budgeting and forecasting analysis to improve efficiency, productivity and profitability.
Identifying and implementing process, system and reporting improvements to enhance accuracy, timeliness and consistency.
Engaging with internal and external stakeholders to communicate insights, support audits, close actions and align delivery objectives.

Demonstrated experience delivering advanced analytics and reporting to support operational, commercial and strategic decision‑making in a complex business environment.
Proven experience within electricity distribution or a similar infrastructure‑based industry, with maintenance and construction activities.
Experience translating complex business requirements and data into actionable insights, recommendations and clear stakeholder communications.
Proven experience working with financial analysis, budgeting, forecasting and performance management to drive productivity and risk‑informed outcomes.
Experience engaging with and influencing senior stakeholders, managing competing priorities and contributing to continuous improvement initiatives.

Job Description

About the role

The Product Manager – Monetisation & Insights (add-ons) creates new add-on products that support hirers across APAC markets. Add-ons are a critical revenue stream that complement job ad campaigns and drive SEEK's long-term monetisation strategy. You will:

Build deep customer segmentation knowledge (by contract value, industry, role mix) to identify hiring needs and product opportunities
Research marketplace add-on strategies and monetised value propositions to inform product decisions
Partner with cross-functional teams to design add-ons that maximize customer value and integrate with ad and non-ad products
Establish feedback loops with customers and sales teams to inform roadmap prioritization

This role requires a marketplace perspective that balances hirer needs with candidate experience. You'll collaborate closely with Commercial, Product Marketing, Strategy, and Sales teams across APAC.

The team

Reporting to the Principal PM – Ad Products and Add-ons, the Product Manager is part of a passionate team working collaboratively with other Product teams, UX, AI Platform Services, Analytics, Engineering, and key stakeholders across Strategy, Commercial Excellence, and Sales to identify and execute on new initiatives. You will manage and drive the product design deliverables (e.g. UX designs, research, user testing) and work within a development team to ensure smooth delivery.

Responsibilities

Own a problem space at the core of transforming and innovating our add-on capabilities to better meet customer needs.
Be central to the transformation of our business model, and be a leader in challenging our status quo.
Actively manage and engage stakeholders across the business to ensure strategic objectives are being met.
Be a relentless customer advocate with a focus on delivering great user experiences that solve real customer problems.
Ideate and validate opportunities and problems, inclusive of strategic fit and financial assessment.
Develop execution plans, and deliver enhancements and new functionality for our Contracted Hirers (working in concert with other relevant teams who also build non-job ad value).
Own key metrics / outcomes related to Contracted Hirers and Insights.
Stay abreast of technology, industry and competitor trends.
Qualifications

Skills and experience

Strategic problem-solver, comfortable working in a space with significant ambiguity.
Structured decision-maker able to consider complex, nuanced tradeoffs, make decisive judgments, and bring others along with you.
Strong customer focus, with a passion for identifying and solving customer needs.
Commercial acumen, able to consider business constraints and objectives.
Strong analytical skills, comfortable with data and working with data scientists to improve the performance of our products.
Ability to lead cross-functional teams to deliver business outcomes.
Able to influence and persuade at all levels of the organisation and build and maintain strong stakeholder relationships.
Considerable experience in product development with solid understanding of agile software development, across customer discovery and delivery.
Experience working with AI and AI teams is an advantage.
Well-developed communication, presentation and interpersonal skills.
Belief in and passion for SEEK’s Purpose.
Additional Information

Annual Performance Bonus Plan
The opportunity to work from anywhere for up to 4 weeks per financial year
Frequent events including sports days, year-end party, hackathon, and trivia
Casual dress every day
